Text:
A dark red door had appeared in the arena after
Shadow made his exit.
What is that...?
Looks like some giant door.
Is a new warrior going to arrive?
We just had that witch... What next, a demon?

This cannot be... Did the Sanctuary respond to
Shadow...?!
Archbishop?
What do you mean by "respond"...?
Oh... Um, well...

As you know, today is the one day of the year when
the doors of the Sanctuary open. However, they have
never shown themselves during the middle of the
Goddess' Trial...

But I had heard that the Sanctuary door was
concealed deep within the church...

The doors I refer to here are not singular objects
that exist in the physical sense.

As you can see here, they change shape and location
freely to best suit those they seek or deem worthy.

It could be the Unsolicited Door, the Beckoning Door,
the Welcoming Door...
The question is, which do we have here...

No! The door is opening! Get the faithful out of here
at once! Do not let anyone approach it!
The Goddess' Trial is canceled!
Please exit the stadium at once!

I must ask that you all leave as well, in the event
that something dreadful might happen...
Rose and Alexia abruptly draw their swords.
Eep...
What is the meaning of—
Y-You must be...the Shadow Garden!
(She's strong...!)

The woman's gaze carries a dreadful intensity, her
presence overwhelming, as if she ruled over the night.

To Rose and Alexia, in their minds Shadow is the most
powerful, but they can both tell from her aura that this
woman is not far from him in strength.

Sorry, but I must ask that you sit still until the
door closes.
I'll leave the rest to you.
Understood, Lady Alpha.
Delta.
Okay.
The woman called Alpha moves toward the door.
She's gone!
Stop, do not enter the Sanctuary!
What are you trying to do?!

We just want you to sit still until the door
disappears.
But...we need baldy to come with us.
What are you people planning to do in the Sanctuary?!

It's not about what we're planning on doing but what
we expect to find.

Her gaze alone is enough to freeze Rose and the
others where they stand. Her eyes are clear as
lakes, focused intently
on the princesses.

This woman is strong too. Not on Alpha's level,
but she has that intensity that only the powerful
possess.
(But...if it comes to this...)
*shocked gasp*
One false move and I can't guarantee her life.

Epsilon's tone suggests she had sensed Rose and
Alexia's hostile intentions. Their eyes are on Natsume,
who has been seized by the black-clad assailants.
Eeek!
Natsume!
We could just let them have her.
Absolutely not!
It's for the best. She's super fake, anyhow.
Absolutely not, I said.
I-I'm fine. Don't worry about me...
Fake.
I know EXACTLY what you mean.
She hears someone's voice but ignores it.
(We can go in whenever we want.)
(But it won't stay open forever, huh...)

We're going inside, too. Come on, cueball. And you,
lady...
If you wish to live, you should go on your own...
to the afterlife, that is!

Nelson fights back, catching Epsilon off guard.
But then…
A black silhouette drops down and slices Epsilon.
She watches herself take the cut with utmost focus.

Despite being caught completely by surprise, Epsilon
is impressively able to jerk back her upper body to
dodge the attack.
But...that also gives rise to tragedy.
*shocked gasp*

Scenes from the past flash through Epsilon's mind
like a kaleidoscope.

Her appearance was important to her, namely because
there was a man who had her love and respect.

She had obsessed over her charms objectively and thus
foresaw a very difficult battle ahead.
I shall grant you power.

The slime bodysuit. Epsilon had been spellbound,
immediately aware of its potential.
She knew she could enhance herself with it.

From then on, Epsilon studied Beta as she would an
enemy, and in the span of a few days had achieved
perfect control of the slime, allowing her to recreate
the right jiggles and textures.

That earned her the nickname The Faithful, and with it
everyone's recognition. But that no longer mattered
to her.
Epsilon shuddered as she observed Beta each day.
(How does she keep getting bigger?!)

This was war. A war without quarter between the
natural and the artificial.

The two softest masses of Epsilon's slime suit hang
in midair.
In that moment, she awakens.

The magic remaining in those airborne masses can be
controlled so they retain their shape.

Her ability to flawlessly manipulate magic removed
from her body is a mind boggling feat.

As she arcs back Epsilon simultaneously pulls the
magic back to herself, instantly affixing the masses
to their original locations.

Maintaining that level of inch-perfect control in the
blink of an eye—it is truly a display of superhuman
talent

Epsilon even throws in a perfect bounce at the end.
That's what makes her The Faithful.
(Not here...!)
(My secret is NOT coming out here!!!)
What's the matter, Venom? Answer me!
Your Executioner...
has already been executed.

Though she had almost certainly been slashed, Epsilon
still stands, completely unharmed.
Did you see anything...?!
I said, did you see anything?
Ahhh... I-I didn't see anything!
Come along, baldy.
What did she think he saw?
Did we miss something in that brief scuffle?
Oh!
Noooo...
Hey!
Natsume!
*gasp*
The door...
It's closing.

Alexia breaks into a dash just before the door shuts
all the way.
Alexia?!
Alexia plunges through the door.
Ohhh, why me?!
Rose chases after her and stumbles through as well.
And then the door closed.
